INDICATOR.INDICATOR_NAME: Employee Lost Time and Restricted Duty Rate
INDICATOR.DESCRIPTION: Lags. An employee lost time injury or illness is one that prevents an employee from returning to work for at least one full shift. The rate is injuries and illnesses per 200,000 worker hours.

Lags. Any injury to a customer as a result of an incident within/on railroad property. Included are injuries that result from an assault or crime. The rate is injuries per million customers. 2012 - the methodology for determining an annual goal was changed. The 2012 goal is based on a 5% reduction of the average prior three year actuals.
The percent of commuter trains that arrive at their destinations within 5 minutes and 59 seconds of the scheduled time.
Average number of miles a railcar travels before a mechanical failure makes the train arrive at its final destination later than 5 minutes and 59 seconds.

The number of passengers from whom the agency receives a fare (cash, train tickets, time-based passes, etc.) Ridership data is preliminary and subject to revision as well as adjustments warranted by annual audit review.
